# Botched shell / redirect fragments (LLM leftovers)
# Created when a command like `node -e "..." > fs.renameSync(path.join(p` is run
# at the repo root with a truncated or mis-quoted redirect — the literal text
# after `>` becomes a filename. Same risk for any node/fs/path/console method
# that ends up accidentally redirected to the project root. The explicit prefix
# rules below are robust against the multiple-paren case (git's pattern
# matcher can be flaky when a filename contains >1 paren), and the broader
# /fs.*, /path.*, /console.* rules catch any other method-call leftovers.
fs.renameSync*
path.join*
console.log*
/fs.*
/path.*
/console.*
*.tmp
*.bak

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Personal / local files
opencode.json
_index_test.py
.claude/settings.local.json
wrap-tools-*.js

